{{#if herokuApp}}
<h2>You need to setup OAUTH and Installed Package</h2>
{{/if}}
{{#if isLocal}}
<h2>You need to create local env file</h2>
{{/if}}
<ol>
   {{#if herokuApp}}
   <li>
      Setup an OAUTH on Salesforce:
      <ol>
         <li><a href="https://login.salesforce.com/app/mgmt/forceCONNECTED_APPs/forceAppEdit.apexp">Create a new Connected App on Salesforce</a></li>
         <li>Fill in the <em>Connected App Name</em>, <em>API Name</em>, and <em>Contact Email</em> fields.</li>
         <li>
            Select <em>Enable OAuth Settings</em> and enter the following <em>Callback URLs</em>: 
            <pre><code>{{oauthCallbackUrl}}
http://localhost:3000</code></pre>
         </li>
         <li>Select <em>Full access (full)</em> from the list of OAuth Scopes and click <em>Add</em></li>
         <li>Click <em>Save</em> and them <em>Continue</em> to complete the creation of the new Connected App</li>
      </ol>
   </li>
   {{/if}}
   <li>
      {{#if herokuApp}}
      Set the <em>Consumer Key</em> and <em>Consumer Secret</em> values in your Heroku app's config:
      <ol>
         <li><a href="https://dashboard.heroku.com/apps/{{herokuApp}}/settings" target="_blank">Open your app's settings</a></li>
         <li>Click <em>Reveal Config Vars</em></li>
         <li>Add a new config var named <code>CONSUMER_KEY</code> with the value of your Connected App's Consumer Key</li>
         <li>Add a new config var named <code>CONSUMER_SECRET</code> with the value of your Connected App's Consumer Secret</li>
      </ol>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if isLocal}}
      Create a new <code>.env</code> file in the root of your project directory containing the following <em>values</em>:
      <pre><code># DO NOT SHARE THIS FILE AND INCLUDE IT IN .gitignore
          
CONSUMER_KEY=YOUR_SALESFORCE_CONNECTED_APP_CONSUMER_KEY

CONSUMER_SECRET=YOUR_SALESFORCE_CONNECTED_APP_CONSUMER_SECRET

MC_CLIENT_ID=YOUR_MARKETING_CLOUD_INSTALLED_PACKAGE_CLIENT_ID

MC_CLIENT_SECRET=YOUR_MARKETING_CLOUD_INSTALLED_PACKAGE_CLIENT_SECRET

MC_AUTHENTICATION_BASE_URI=YOUR_MARKETING_CLOUD_INSTALLED_PACKAGE_AUTHENTICATION_BASE_URI

MC_REST_BASE_URI=YOUR_MARKETING_CLOUD_INSTALLED_PACKAGE_REST_BASE_URI</code></pre>
      {{/if}}
   </li>
   {{#if herokuApp}}
   <li>
      Setup an Installed Package in Marketing Cloud:
      <ol>
         <li><a href="https://mc.s10.exacttarget.com/cloud/#app/Setup/InstalledPackages">Create a new Installed Package in Marketing Cloud</a></li>
         <li>Fill in the <em>Package Name</em> and <em>Description</em> fields and save the package.</li>
         <li>Under Components, click <em>Add Component</em> and Select <em>API Integration</em> and Select <em>Server-to-Server integration</em> type.</li>
         <li>Click <em>Save</em> and them <em>Continue</em> to complete the creation of the new Installed Package.</li>
         <li>Define the scope properties for the integration the properties for the integration, check everything under <em>Assets</em> section.</li>
      </ol>
   </li>
   {{/if}}
   {{#if herokuApp}}
   <li>
      Set the <em>Client Id</em>, <em>Client Secret</em>, <em>Authentication Base URI</em> and <em>REST Base URI</em> values in your Heroku app's config:
      <ol>
         <li><a href="https://dashboard.heroku.com/apps/{{herokuApp}}/settings" target="_blank">Open your app's settings</a></li>
         <li>Click <em>Reveal Config Vars</em></li>
         <li>Add a new config var named <code>MC_CLIENT_ID</code> with the value of your Installed Package's Client Id</li>
         <li>Add a new config var named <code>MC_CLIENT_SECRET</code> with the value of your Installed Package's Client Secret</li>
         <li>Add a new config var named <code>MC_AUTHENTICATION_BASE_URI</code> with the value of your Installed Package's Authentication Base URI</li>
         <li>Add a new config var named <code>MC_REST_BASE_URI</code> with the value of your Installed Package's REST Base URI</li>
      </ol>
   </li>
   {{/if}}
   <li>
      Refresh this page
   </li>
</ol>
